@*
    The authenticated app shell: a nav rail, a breadcrumb topbar, and a scrolling main. All nav,
    authorization, and entitlement logic lives in ShellNavResolver behind the view components; this
    layout owns only the frame. The rail collapses to a focus-trapping drawer below the desktop
    breakpoint (railDrawer, app.js): Escape closes it and restores focus to the opener (A5), and the
    background stage is held inert while it is open so focus cannot land on the obscured page.
*@
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<partial name="_Head" />
<body class="font-sans text-ink">
<div class="fb-app" x-data="railDrawer" @@keydown.escape.window="hide()">
    <div class="fb-scrim" x-show="open" x-cloak @@click="hide()"></div>
    <vc:shell-rail />
    <div class="fb-stage" :inert="open || null">
        <vc:shell-topbar />
        <main class="fb-main" tabindex="-1">
            @RenderBody()
        </main>
    </div>
    @* Third sibling of the rail and stage: the palette holds those two inert while open and is itself
       outside that list, so it stays reachable. Coupled to the rail opener through the "palette" store. *@
    <vc:shell-palette />
</div>
</body>
</html>
